Udev rules are used to assign specific device names to hardware, e.g. webcams, arduinos, etc.

A useful guide is available at
http://www.reactivated.net/writing_udev_rules.html
http://hackaday.com/2009/09/18/how-to-write-udev-rules/

To install the rules:

1) Copy *.rules files into the /etc/udev/rules.d/ directory
2) At the command line, type: 'sudo service udev restart'

or run the bash script "install_rules.sh"
